DOCUMENT();       

loadMacros("PG.pl",
           "PGbasicmacros.pl",
           "PGchoicemacros.pl",
           "PGanswermacros.pl",
           "PGgraphmacros.pl",
           "extraAnswerEvaluators.pl",
           "PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl",
           "PGgraphmacros.pl"
           );
       
TEXT(beginproblem()); # standard preamble to each problem.


$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

@x = (5,15,30,60,120,240,480,720,1440,2880,5760,10080);
@y = (73,61.7,58.3,55.7,50.3,46.7,40.3,38.3,29.0,24.0,18.7,10.3);

$n = 12;
for ($j = 0; $j <= $n-1; $j++) {$ln_x[$j] = ln($x[$j])/ln(exp(1));
                                $rd_lnx[$j] = round($ln_x[$j]*10000)/10000;
};

for ($j = 0; $j <=5; $j++){
           $x_top[$j] = $x[$j]; $x_bot[$j] = $x[$j+6];
           $y_top[$j] = $y[$j]; $y_bot[$j] = $y[$j+6];
           $rd_xtop[$j] = $rd_lnx[$j]; $rd_xbot[$j] = $rd_lnx[$j+6]};

$sum_x = 0;
$sum_y = 0;
$sum_lnx = 0;
$sum_prod = 0;
$sum_lnxprod = 0;
$sum_xsq = 0;
$sum_ysq = 0;
$sum_lnxsq = 0;

for ($i = 0; $i <= $n-1; $i++){
                             $sum_x = $sum_x + $x[$i];
                             $sum_y = $sum_y + $y[$i];
                             $sum_prod = $sum_prod + $x[$i]*$y[$i]; 
                             $sum_xsq = $sum_xsq + $x[$i]**2;
                             $sum_ysq = $sum_ysq + $y[$i]**2;
                             $sum_lnx = $sum_lnx + $ln_x[$i];
                             $sum_lnxprod = $sum_lnxprod + $ln_x[$i]*$y[$i]; 
                             $sum_lnxsq = $sum_lnxsq + $ln_x[$i]**2;
};

$b = ($n*$sum_prod - $sum_x * $sum_y)/($n*$sum_xsq - $sum_x**2);
$a = ($sum_y - $sum_x*$b)/$n;
$rd_b = round($b*10000)/10000;
$rd_a = round($a*10000)/10000;

$ln_b = ($n*$sum_lnxprod - $sum_lnx * $sum_y)/($n*$sum_lnxsq - $sum_lnx**2);
$ln_a = ($sum_y - $sum_lnx*$ln_b)/$n;
$rd_lnb = round($ln_b*10000)/10000;
$rd_lna = round($ln_a*10000)/10000;

$none = round( exp(-$ln_a/$ln_b)/1440);
$all = round( 60*exp((100-$ln_a)/$ln_b));

BEGIN_TEXT
Question 20:
$BR $SPACE $BR
To study how recognition memory decreases with time, the following
experiment was conducted.  The subject read a list of 20 words slowly
aloud, and later, at different time intervals, was shown a list of 40
words containing the 20 words that he or she had read.  The
percentage, $BITALIC P${EITALIC}, of words recognized was recorded as a function of $BITALIC t${EITALIC}, the time elapsed in minutes.  The table below shows the
averages for 5 different subjects.  This is modeled by \( P=a\ln t +b \).

$BR $SPACE $BR
$BCENTER
\{ begintable(7) \}
\{ row( "$SPACE $SPACE t, min $SPACE $SPACE", @x_top ) \}
\{ row( "$SPACE $SPACE P${PERCENT} $SPACE $SPACE", @y_top ) \}
\{ endtable() \}
$BR
\{ begintable(7) \}
\{ row( "$SPACE $SPACE t, min $SPACE $SPACE", @x_bot ) \}
\{ row( "$SPACE $SPACE P${PERCENT} $SPACE $SPACE", @y_bot ) \}
\{ endtable() \}
$ECENTER
$BR $SPACE $BR
a) Find \( \ln{t} \) for each value of \( t \) in the table above, and then use linear regression on a calculator to estimate \( a \) and \( b \) in the linear fit \( P= a \ln{t} +b \).  In the blanks below, enter the corresponding values for \( a \) and \( b \): $BR
\( \ \ \ \ a = \) \{ ans_rule(20) \}  \( \ \ \ \ \ \ \ b = \) \{ ans_rule(20) \} (round values to 4 decimal places)
$BR $SPACE $BR
b) When does this model (in part a) predict that the subjects will recognize no words? $BR
$SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE In \{ ans_rule(20) \} DAYS (1440 minutes = 1 day)
$BR $SPACE $BR
c) When does this model (in part a) predict that the subjects will recognize all words? $BR
$SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE In \{ ans_rule(20) \} SECONDS.
END_TEXT

###### a is now b and b is a ##########
ANS(num_cmp( $rd_lnb,tol=>0.001) );
ANS(num_cmp( $rd_lna,tol=>0.001) );
ANS(num_cmp( $none,tol=>1.5) );
ANS(num_cmp( $all,tol=>1.5) );

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$BR $SPACE $BR 
$BBOLD  SOLUTION $EBOLD
$BR
a) Find the values of \( \ln t \) in the table, use linear regression on \( \ln{t} \) and \( P \).  The line has slope \( -7.787 \) and \( P \)-intercept 86.283 \( P=-7.787 \ln{t} + 86.283 \).  
$BR $SPACE $BR
Thus \( a=-7.787 \) and \( b=86.283 \).
$BR $SPACE $BR
b) The subjects will recognize no words when \( P=0 \), that is, when
\( -7.787 \ln{t} + 86.283=0 \).  Solving for \( t \): $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ -7.787 \ \ln{t} = -86.283 \) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ \ln{t} = \frac{86.283}{7.787} \) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ e^{\ln{t}} = e^{(86.283)/(7.787)} \) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ t \approx 64,918.342 \) $BR
so \( t \approx 45 \) days.
$BR $SPACE $BR
c) The subject recognized all the words when \( P=100 \), that is, when
\( -7.787 \ln{t} + 86.283=100 \).  Solving for \( t \):
$BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ -7.787 \ln{t} = 13.717 \) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ \ln{t} = \frac{13.717}{-7.787} \) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ t \approx 0.172 \) , $BR 
so \( t \approx 0.172 \) minutes (about 10 seconds) from the start of the
experiment.
$BR
END_SOLUTION

